                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-01-12</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>As a die-hard lifetime (and long suffering) Red Sox fan, I thought this 2004 World Series DVD was well done and a great addtion to any Red Sox fan's DVD library.  
<br />
<br />My expectations for the DVD certainly weren't very high - I wasn't immediately impressed with MLB using Denis Leary as the narrator - but I have to admit that Leary does a good job in the film.  The pace is very good and more time is spent on the memorable American League Championship Series than I had expected, although even more time should have been spent on the Red Sox' historic victory over the Evil Empire.  God Bless 'em.
<br />
<br />The best part of the DVD for me were the extras. Included are the ALCS Game 4 Walk Off Home Run by David Ortiz, as well as his RBI to win ALCS Game 5.  I've rerun these two hits over and over this winter -- it just warms the heart.  Also included are the last outs of the ALCS and World Series as well as the post-game celebrations.
<br />
<br />The interviews with Red Sox legends Carlton Fisk, Dwight Evans and Fred Lynn were terrific and added a real sense of history to the Red Sox miracle World Series' victory.
<br />
<br />All in all, MLB did a good job on this DVD. Red Sox fans will love it.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Nice Job MLB</div>
